---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Bridger | Levenhall" description="Bridger is Levenhall's pre-RFP intelligence platform for US federal contracting.">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="b-hero">
        <div class="b-hero-glow"></div>
        <div class="b-hero-stage">
            <p class="b-hero-tag">A Levenhall Product</p>
            <img src="/images/products/bridger-logo.png" alt="Bridger" class="b-hero-logo">
            <p class="b-hero-tagline">Market entry intelligence for US federal contracting.</p>
            <div class="b-hero-cta">
                <a href="https://bridger.levenhall.com" class="btn btn-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Bridger</a>
                <a href="https://bridger.levenhall.com/brief" class="btn btn-outline-white" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Daily Brief</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── OPENING ── -->
    <section class="b-opening">
        <div class="b-prose reveal">
            <p class="b-lede">The US government will spend roughly $750 billion this year. By the time any of it shows up on SAM.gov, it has already been decided.</p>
            <p>Appropriations bills, committee markups, agency forecasts, GAO bid protests, OFAC entity-list updates &mdash; the signal that decides who wins moves six to twelve months ahead of the RFP. Incumbents pay fifty thousand dollars a year for that signal. Everyone else competes blind.</p>
            <p>For allied technology firms it is worse. They arrive cold into a regulatory landscape they don't speak, and the partners who could shorten the path are invisible without a local network.</p>
            <p class="b-lede-close">Bridger is the platform we built so they don't have to.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── STRUCTURE ── -->
    <section class="b-structure">
        <div class="b-structure-frame">
            <header class="b-structure-head reveal">
                <span class="b-eyebrow b-eyebrow-light">§ Structure</span>
                <h2>A three-part system, in the order it works.</h2>
            </header>

            <article class="b-block reveal">
                <span class="b-block-num">I</span>
                <div>
                    <h3>Intelligence</h3>
                    <p>About twenty-three hundred procurement signals flow into the index every week &mdash; SAM.gov, FPDS, GAO, OFAC, Congress.gov, agency forecasts, allied defense ministries, the Federal Register.</p>
                    <p>A clustering layer synthesizes them into roughly a thousand confidence-rated assessments. A Country Instability Index scores the markets that matter. Every opportunity is matched against a contractor's profile across five separate signals, and the system will not generate a rationale unless at least two of them actually fired.</p>
                </div>
            </article>

            <article class="b-block reveal">
                <span class="b-block-num">II</span>
                <div>
                    <h3>Marketplace</h3>
                    <p>Three search surfaces on one fit-scoring engine. <strong>Providers</strong> &mdash; C3PAOs, proposal writers, incorporation specialists, JV partners, manufacturers. <strong>Lobbyists</strong> by specialty. <strong>Tech Scout</strong> for the fourteen hundred allied technology firms vetted across sixty-plus countries.</p>
                    <p>Warm introductions at the point of intent. Not a directory you have to remember to open.</p>
                </div>
            </article>

            <article class="b-block reveal">
                <span class="b-block-num">III</span>
                <div>
                    <h3>Capture</h3>
                    <p>A pipeline that knows what stage you're in. An AI-generated capture brief built from the opportunity, the profile, and the match intelligence. A capability statement and past performance auto-filled from one canonical record, so nothing drifts.</p>
                    <p>The distance between <em>I'm watching this</em> and <em>I'm submitting on this</em>, closed.</p>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── ALLIED MOAT ── -->
    <section class="b-moat">
        <div class="b-prose reveal">
            <span class="b-eyebrow">§ The allied moat</span>
            <h2>The compliance regimes other tools won't touch.</h2>
            <p>Bridger indexes the regulatory regimes that govern who can sell what, side by side: <span class="b-tag-inline">🇺🇸 ITAR</span> with AUKUS Final Rule (§ 126.7) eligibility, <span class="b-tag-inline">🇺🇸 FOCI</span> and <span class="b-tag-inline">🇺🇸 CFIUS</span>, <span class="b-tag-inline">🇺🇸 ECCN</span> and BIS licensing, <span class="b-tag-inline">🇦🇺 DSGL</span> and <span class="b-tag-inline">🇦🇺 DISP</span> on the Australian side, <span class="b-tag-inline">🇬🇧 List X</span> on the UK side.</p>
            <p class="b-moat-foot">No general procurement tool tracks these together. That's the layer that makes allied entry tractable.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── DIFFERENTIATION ── -->
    <section class="b-diff">
        <div class="b-diff-frame">
            <header class="b-diff-head reveal">
                <span class="b-eyebrow">§ The short version</span>
                <h2>What you get that you can't get elsewhere.</h2>
            </header>
            <div class="b-diff-rows reveal">
                <div class="b-diff-row b-diff-headrow">
                    <span></span>
                    <span>Bridger</span>
                    <span>Most procurement tools</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Signal timing</span>
                    <span>Pre-RFP signal, forecasts, appropriations</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">RFP listings after SAM.gov publishes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Matching</span>
                    <span>5-signal scoring with cited rationales</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">Keyword search</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Cross-border</span>
                    <span>ITAR / FOCI / CFIUS / DSGL / DISP indexed together</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">US-only</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Marketplace</span>
                    <span>Warm intros inside the intelligence</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">Standalone directory or separate CRM</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Audience</span>
                    <span>Allied technology firms entering the US</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">US-only contractors</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection
        heading="Open Bridger."
        description="Production at bridger.levenhall.com. Free daily brief at 6 AM Eastern."
        primaryLabel="Open Bridger"
        primaryHref="https://bridger.levenhall.com"
        secondaryLabel="Daily Brief"
        secondaryHref="https://bridger.levenhall.com/brief"
    />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ───────────── HERO ───────────── */
    .b-hero {
        background:
            radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 50%, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.08), transparent 70%),
            #060c18;
        padding: var(--s-20) var(--s-3) var(--s-12);
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .b-hero-glow {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        width: 720px;
        height: 720px;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.18) 0%, transparent 60%);
        filter: blur(40px);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .b-hero::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold), transparent);
        opacity: 0.4;
    }

    .b-hero-stage {
        text-align: center;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .b-hero-tag {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        letter-spacing: 3.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: var(--s-6);
    }

    .b-hero-logo {
        max-width: 360px;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
        filter: drop-shadow(0 0 40px rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.25));
    }

    .b-hero-tagline {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
        line-height: 1.5;
        letter-spacing: -0.2px;
        max-width: 520px;
        margin: 0 0 var(--s-8);
    }

    .b-hero-cta {
        display: flex;
        gap: var(--s-2);
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    /* ───────────── SHARED RHYTHM ───────────── */
    .b-prose {
        max-width: var(--col-prose);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 var(--s-3);
    }

    .b-eyebrow {
        display: block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 2.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
    }

    .b-eyebrow-light {
        color: var(--gold);
    }

    /* All h2 across the page */
    .b-opening h2,
    .b-structure h2,
    .b-moat h2,
    .b-diff h2,
    .b-lede,
    .b-lede-close {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        letter-spacing: -0.6px;
    }

    /* ───────────── OPENING ───────────── */
    .b-opening {
        background: var(--cream);
        padding: var(--s-16) 0;
    }

    .b-lede {
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin: 0 0 var(--s-6);
        letter-spacing: -0.4px;
    }

    .b-opening p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin: 0 0 var(--s-4);
    }

    .b-lede-close {
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--burgundy);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding-top: var(--s-5);
        margin-top: var(--s-5);
    }

    /* ───────────── STRUCTURE (DARK) ───────────── */
    .b-structure {
        background: #0a1628;
        padding: var(--s-16) 0;
        position: relative;
    }

    .b-structure::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.25);
    }

    .b-structure-frame {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 var(--s-3);
    }

    .b-structure-head {
        margin-bottom: var(--s-10);
        padding-bottom: var(--s-6);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .b-structure-head h2 {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.4vw, 2.6rem);
        line-height: 1.18;
        color: #fff;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .b-block {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr;
        gap: var(--s-6);
        padding: var(--s-8) 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    }

    .b-block:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }

    .b-block-num {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: -1px;
        padding-top: 0.4rem;
    }

    .b-block h3 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 1.65rem;
        color: #fff;
        margin: 0 0 var(--s-3);
        line-height: 1.25;
        letter-spacing: -0.4px;
    }

    .b-block p {
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
        margin: 0 0 var(--s-3);
    }

    .b-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .b-block strong { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
    .b-block em { font-style: italic; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85); }

    /* ───────────── MOAT ───────────── */
    .b-moat {
        background: var(--stone);
        padding: var(--s-16) 0;
    }

    .b-moat h2 {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3.2vw, 2.4rem);
        line-height: 1.2;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
    }

    .b-moat p {
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        line-height: 2;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
    }

    .b-tag-inline {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
        margin: 0 0.1rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .b-moat-foot {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--burgundy);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding-top: var(--s-5);
        margin-top: var(--s-5);
    }

    /* ───────────── DIFFERENTIATION ───────────── */
    .b-diff {
        background: var(--cream);
        padding: var(--s-16) 0;
    }

    .b-diff-frame {
        max-width: 980px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 var(--s-3);
    }

    .b-diff-head {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: var(--col-prose);
        margin: 0 auto var(--s-10);
    }

    .b-diff-head h2 {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3.2vw, 2.4rem);
        line-height: 1.2;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
    }

    .b-diff-rows {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .b-diff-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.7fr 1.4fr 1fr;
        gap: var(--s-5);
        padding: var(--s-4) 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(30, 58, 95, 0.1);
        align-items: center;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .b-diff-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .b-diff-headrow {
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--deep-navy);
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--text-medium);
    }

    .b-diff-headrow span:nth-child(2) { color: var(--burgundy); }

    .b-diff-cap {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 1.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
    }

    .b-diff-other {
        color: var(--text-medium);
        font-style: italic;
    }

    /* ───────────── RESPONSIVE ───────────── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .b-hero { padding: var(--s-16) var(--s-3) var(--s-10); min-height: auto; }
        .b-hero-logo { max-width: 300px; }
        .b-hero-tagline { font-size: 1.15rem; }
        .b-opening, .b-structure, .b-moat, .b-diff { padding: var(--s-12) 0; }
        .b-lede { font-size: 1.4rem; }
        .b-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--s-3); padding: var(--s-6) 0; }
        .b-block-num { font-size: 2rem; padding-top: 0; }
        .b-diff-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--s-1); padding: var(--s-3) 0; }
        .b-diff-headrow { display: none; }
        .b-diff-cap { color: var(--burgundy); }
    }
</style>
